# Install Bind9, Basic Configuration

# Bind9 Installation

sudo apt update
sudo apt install bind9

# Bind9 Configuration

vim /etc/bind/named.conf.options

listen-on { any; };
allow-query { any; };

forwarders {
    8.8.8.8;
    1.1.1.1;
};

# Post Configuration

sudo named-checkconf                # Checks config file for errors
sudo systemctl restart bind9        # Restarts the bind9 service

# Info

The bind9 config can be found under: /etc/bind/named.conf.options
If you use firewall you will need to allow bind9